  "prompt": "I'm in love with my FWB, should I stop having sex with him cause every time we have sex I get more attached to him?",
  "response": "Navigating feelings in a friends-with-benefits (FWB) situation can be complicated. Here are a few things to consider that might help you make a decision:\n\n1. **Acknowledging Your Feelings:** It's important to recognize and accept your feelings. If you are falling in love, this is a significant shift from the casual arrangement you originally had.\n\n2. **Communicating:** Have an honest conversation with your FWB about your feelings. It's possible they may feel the same way, or they might not. Understanding where both of you stand can help in deciding the future of your relationship.\n\n3. **Assessing Your Needs:** Consider what you really want: a committed relationship, or to continue with the casual setup. If your emotional needs are no longer being met by a FWB arrangement, it may be time to make changes.\n\n4. **Protecting Yourself:** If continuing to have sex is leading to deeper attachment and emotional pain, it might be healthier to step back from the physical aspect. Focus on what will be best for your emotional well-being.\n\n5. **Exploring Other Options:** You might want to allow some space and explore other relationships. Sometimes taking a break can give you clarity and perspective.\n\n6. **Seeking Support:** talking to friends, family, or a therapist can provide a helpful outside perspective on your situation.\n\nUltimately, it's important to prioritize your emotional health and make a decision that aligns with your personal needs and desires.",
